summary: Hi, I’ve been seeing some people claim that Sansa doesn’t care about her family? I’ve never read the books but is this true? :(
question: Hi, I’ve been seeing some people claim that Sansa doesn’t care about her family? I’ve never read the books but is this true? :(
answer:
No, of course it isn’t true. This discourse is just one instance of fandom wank against Sansa meant to start arguments.

In the past we’ve had fanboys from reddit and worg deliberately start arguments this way and then get together and repost and laugh at the responses they get from Tumblr Sansa fans. So we don’t typically join these discussions.

For more discussion, @nobodysuspectsthebutterfly @asoiafuniversity and @thebluelemontree all have excellent meta on Sansa Stark and her relationships with her parents and siblings.

Sansa worries about, misses, and remembers happier times with her family throughout the asoiaf series, even when she is posing as Alayne. And unlike on the show (or some got/asoiaf fans) neither Arya nor the rest of her siblings ever blame her for her actions in King’s Landing.
